<h1>LTI Javascript app wrapper</h1>

<p>This server application turns any Javascript app into an <a href="http://www.imsglobal.org/LTI/v1p1/ltiIMGv1p1.html">IMS LTI 1.1</a> tool provider. <a href="https://www.edu-apps.org">Edu Apps</a> has a good <a href="https://www.edu-apps.org/code.html">description of how LTI works</a>.</p>

<p>The benefits of serving your Javascript app as an LTI Tool instead of a simple page are:</p>

<ul class="task-list">
<li>Your Javascript app will know the identity of the learner, passed from the LTI Tool Consumer</li>
<li>Your app can send a result back to the LTI Tool Consumer at the end with the learner's percentage grade</li>
<li>You can launch it from an LTI Tool Consumer such as <a href="https://tech.coursera.org/app-platform/lti/">Coursera</a>
</li>
</ul>

<p>This web app provides some additional benefits:</p>

<ul class="task-list">
<li>Your configure your web page content using forms instead of file uploads</li>
<li>Your Javascript app is provided functions to log in a common format</li>
<li>You can download the log data from this web application</li>
</ul>


